Timeswap brings an additional layer of decentralisation by explicitly giving control to users to decide their own risk vs reward profile

Market participants across the risk spectrum can pool together in one pool and greatly improve liquidity as well as capital efficiency https://t.co/pZyCyeHXJZ

One of primary goal at Timeswap is to improve  capital efficiency.

Timeswap's fixed maturity pools can be used to create money markets for any ERC-20 token pair. Interest rates & collateralization ratios are market driven and all of this is achieved without using an Oracle. https://t.co/a8oyTE5TAX

Capital Efficiency in DeFi refers to how efficiently a protocol is utilising its liquidity. Liquidity is supplied by liquidity providers in DeFi protocols and every protocol should aim to maximize the capital efficiency which in turn enables more efficient pricing for users. https://t.co/1joiGAKIBa
